
                  ~ evee.js ~

    Tiny, cross-browser, modern event binding
    micro-library with support for leakless
    data-handler binding and triggering events.
    Inspired by https://github.com/arextar/Vine.

    Example usage:

      evee.bind(elem, 'click', function(ev) {
        assert(this === elem);
        assert(ev.data === data);
        assert(ev.target === elem);
      }, data);

      evee.unbind(elem, 'click', handler);

      // simulate a cancellable mouse click
      evee.trigger(elem, 'click');

    Installation via bower:

      $ bower install eugene-eeo/evee.js
